HEADWORD: Stenography
<hw>Ste*nog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>steno`s</grk> narrow, close + <ets>graphy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>st⟦eacute⟧nographie</ets>, G. <ets>stenographie</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The art of writing in shorthand, by using abbreviations or
characters for whole words; shorthand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

